text: Kunchukokhabl () is a rural locality (an aul) in Dzhidzhikhablskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 519 as of 2018. There are 10 streets. == Geography == The aul is on the shore of the Gulf of Krasnodar reservoir, 8 km east from the Dzhidzhikhabl aul. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Kunchukokhabl
